6: What do you mean I can't go?!
10:
And after all I've done for you,
Marina! I can't believe it!
13:
First you didn't invite me to your
sweet summer getaway, now THIS!
18:
Oh Amelia, sweetie, don't take it so
personally! Just think about it for a
second.
20:
You're a mermaid! People don't
know your kind exists. Imagine what
would happen if you got found out!
30:
This isn't like you, Marina! I thought
the Crimson Blades were all about,
like, paving their own path and stuff!
33:
I mean, we are, but that doesn't
mean we throw all rules out the
window!
35:
But when you put it that way... You
DID put in a lot of work for us this
time around.
44:
All right then, I cave! Let's go on a
date!
55:
Wow it's just like in my dreams.
We're actually going on a date!
59:
Only until the sun comes up though,
all right? I figure we're safe until then.
66:
Hey, Marina, what's that weird statue
over there?
74:
Yep. Her happiness is infectious, isn't
it?
76:
I'm glad she got the chance to do
this.
81:
Stellie! Al! Get over here, you
slowpokes!
85:
Are you sure you want us tagging
along, Amelia? We don't want to get
in the way of your date.
89:
The more, the merrier, Al! This way is
more fun!
95:
I love it when you say adorable
things like that, Amelia! Hehe.
105: For what it's worth, I think so too.
114:
Ohmygosh. So many fans all of a
sudden—I don't know what to say!
119:
A date at an actual cafe! This is
perfect!
122:
I'm so happy I could just turn to sea
foam!
125:
You do love being dramatic, don't
you? But, uh, why foam exactly?
130:
Oh, I just read it in a book! When a
mermaid dies, they turn into sea
foam. Actually, that's not true for
mermaids like myself, but still.
135:
Is that the story where the mermaid
meets a prince, but loses her voice?
That never did make much sense to
me...
140:
Yes! That one! I have a complicated
relationship with that book.
144: How do you know it, Alk?
148:
Me? I think I found it lying around
Starview Village's library at one
point.
152:
Hmm. I gotta say, I can empathize
with the whole "leg envy" bit.
However, I am absolutely NOT okay
with losing my voice!
155:
The world would be a very quiet
place...
159:
What's that supposed to mean? Are
you saying I'm loud?
164:
Then it's settled—the next treasure
we go after needs to be something
that'll grow legs on a mermaid!
167:
That sounds like it would involve
some serious forbidden magic...
170:
No biggie. "Forbidden" is just a
suggestion anyway!
175:
Yeah! Besides, I really want to wear
slim-fit pants!
179: I would like to see that.
183: Oh, it's dawn already? Darn it.
186:
Parting is such sweet sorrow, or
however the saying goes.
195:
Remember how I told you I could get
back to my home world easily?
202:
Well, here's the thing. I may have
exaggerated ever so slightly.
205:
I've been looking for a way to get
back ever since we last spoke, and
uh... I haven't found one.
208:
Which probably means...
There might not be a way for me to
get back home.
217:
But you know what? If I've got more
incredible days like today waiting for
me... I think I can find the strength to
carry on.
220:
Alk, Stella... I hope you'll stick around
with me.
225: We will. I want to go on another date.
229:
Of course, we can't skip out on the
dates. With Amelia too.
235:
Here's to even more adventures
together!
